strings.Value: "Fine, open the gates."
[Leave] "I have no time for this nonsense."
[Attack] "I'll feed your beast… with your corpse, goblin."
[Leave] "Feed your animals yourself."
"What did you call me?"
"Deal, I'll do it."
"What is this task?"
"Missions require I be paid first."
"Won't this animal attack me?"
[Attack] "Let me show you how angry I am."
[Leave] "Why am I wasting my time on you?"
"We can always kill him later. Let's hear him out."
[Attack] "Ha ha ha! Go on! Burn him!"
"Hide your weapon and shut your mouth. I'm almost as sick of your disorderly conduct as I am of your stupid jokes!"
"Put your weapon away. Why do you even need it? Your puns alone will kill them!"
"Hey — hey, you, potion-gulper! Like questes? Going on misshuns? I have a one for you!"
"Awchhh! Heh-heee… no believe it, the beastie attacked? No! Who have thought! Heh-heee… you not angry? Yes?"
"Well, you real hero, I sees it! Go in, play with him, I bring food right away!"
"Potion-gulper! Like, sword-swinger! Like, bow-shooter! One of those who go run around woods, go deep in caves, on misshuns and questes like that!"
"Really? That be great… Hey!" {n}The goblin looks strangely indignant.{/n} "You not even ask what the misshun IS!"

"Short tale, make shorter! See — beastie in cage? My fren and I looking after him. We divide work — I open gate, fren goes in, feeds the beastie. Got it?" {n}The goblin glances around, slightly irritated.{/n} "But he be lazy, go away. What I offer is open gate, you go inside — give beastie food!"
"PFfft! You no hero, only name hero, worst hero!"
"Change mind, huh? It good musshun, promise! You like it!"
"You be such a greedy fingers! What can give you…" {n}The goblin glances around.{/n} "Nothing, nothing, nothing! But…" {n}His eyes gleam.{/n} "...you have an expar-ince you not unforget!"
"No-no-no, nothing like that! He be just a pet! Like slug or spider… small spider. Or grot snake!" {n}He pauses.{/n} "Little grot snake?"
"Heh, now that's just the kind of language the old legends need! Just imagine — 'This is the saga of Tormund, brave potion-gulper, who ran around in the woods doing misshuns'... Amazing, ha ha!"
"Are we running errands for goblins now? Please tell me you are not serious."
"You hear that? Why, he's a natural-born book publisher! You wouldn't believe how many times I found myself sitting in their posh studies, listening to these exact words!"
"You can't be serious."
"Angry? At you? You're not worth my anger. You merely annoy me — and that's reason enough to kill you."
"Dooon't!"
"Running missions for this freak? I'd rather chop him to pieces and... gobble 'em up! Ha ha!" {n}Regongar smirks menacingly as he reaches for his weapon.{/n}
"Heh... Gobble 'em up, get it? Hmm..." {n}Realizing no one liked his pun, Regongar scowls and spits on the ground.{/n}
{n}With a guffaw, the half-orc takes his hand off his weapon, but he keeps watching the goblin menacingly.{/n}
"Fine, fine... Was it something I said?" {n}Grumbling, the half-orc spits on the ground.{/n}
